Infographic: Kerala is the best state for newborn children 
4-3-2017 
Kerala is the best state for newborn children

Kerala has set the bar for the rest of India by bringing down the infant mortality rate — the number of children under the age of 1 who die for every 1,000 born — to six.This is at par with several developed countries, according to the recently released National Family Health Survey. Here’s a look at how some other states fare on this parameter. 
